  "texts": [
    "Each commit on GitHub is a record of a modification to the source code, capturing the specific changes made, along with metadata such as the author's name, a timestamp, and a message describing the purpose of the change.",
    "The natural experiment that our investigation exploits is the launch of GitHub Copilot, an AI-powered LLM that provides coding assistance.",
    "GitHub Copilot, developed collaboratively by GitHub and OpenAI, was unveiled in October 2021.",
    "Upon its official launch, GitHub Copilot selectively supported certain programming languages, including Python and Rust, while not supporting others such as R and Haskell.",
    "By the end of 2022, ChatGPT was launched and by 2023 GitHub Copilot eventually broadened its support to include previously unsupported languages like R (see Figure 2)."
  ],
